# Red Hat Brand Standards

When generating UI, CSS, or documentation, adhere strictly to these Red Hat guidelines.

## 1. Color Palette (Core)
- **Red Hat Red:** `#ee0000` (Brand identity only — never for errors or danger states).
- **Dark Red:** `#cc0000` (Gradients and hover states paired with Red Hat Red).
- **UX Black:** `#151515`.
- **White:** `#ffffff`.

## 2. Extended Neutrals
- **Light Grey:** `#f5f5f5` (Backgrounds, cards, alternating rows).
- **Dark Grey:** `#595959` (Secondary text, captions).

## 3. Contextual Colors
- **Success:** `#3d7317` (success-green-60).
- **Error/Danger:** `#f0561d` (danger-orange-50).
- **Warning:** `#f8ce1c` (yellow-30).
- **Info/Links:** `#0066cc` (interaction-blue-50).

## 4. Typography
- **Headings:** Use 'Red Hat Display'.
- **Body:** Use 'Red Hat Text'.
- **Code:** Use 'Red Hat Mono'.
- **Alignment:** Always flush left. Avoid justified text.
- **Casing:** Use sentence case for headlines and buttons (e.g., "Get started" not "Get Started").
- **Google Fonts loading:**
  ```html
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Red+Hat+Display:wght@400;700&family=Red+Hat+Text:wght@400;700&family=Red+Hat+Mono:wght@400;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  ```

## 5. Icons
- **UI Icons:** Use for navigation/utility. Stroke weight 2px on a 32px grid.
- **Tech Icons:**
  - Products: Black rounded rectangle background.
  - Components: White rounded rectangle background.

## 6. Accessibility
- Minimum body text: 12px (0.75rem at 16px base).
- Never use colour alone to convey meaning — add labels, patterns, or icons.
- Dark-on-light contrast must meet WCAG AA (4.5:1 for text, 3:1 for large text/UI).

## 7. Dark Backgrounds
- On dark panels (`#151515` or `#1a1a1a`), use white (`#ffffff`) text and `#ee0000` for accent borders/highlights.
- For print, provide a light-mode fallback (white card with red left border) so dark panels remain readable.

## 8. Print / PDF
- Always include `print-color-adjust: exact; -webkit-print-color-adjust: exact;` on coloured backgrounds, borders, and text in `@media print` blocks.
- Use `@page { margin: 0; size: A4 landscape; }` for slide-based exports.
- Hide navigation and progress UI in print.

## 9. Documentation Sources
- Brand Standards: https://www.redhat.com/en/about/brand/standards
- UI Icons: https://www.redhat.com/en/about/brand/standards/icons/ui-icons
- Tech Icons: https://www.redhat.com/en/about/brand/standards/icons/technology-icons
